<div id="intro-text-container">
  <p>
A wontology is a <u>w</u>iki-<u>ontology</u>: a publicly editable
store of information in lists, trees, hierarchies, and relationships.
To get started:
  </p><ul>
    <li>read <a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:InformationAsRelationships">Information as Relationships</a>, or</li>
    <li>do our <a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:Tutorials/CreatingANode">first tutorial</a>.</li>
  </ul><p>
<em>You are welcome to experiment with this system and its data</em>, to
add new information, and to expand or edit what is already present.
  </p><p>
For more information, see

<a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:WontologyConcepts">Wontology Concepts</a>,

<a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:NamingConventions">Naming Conventions</a>, and

<a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:AboutWontologyOrg">About wontology.org</a>.

This wontology contains information for many different subject areas.
You can simply browse from the links below, or start from

<a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:BrowsingAWontology">Browsing a Wontology</a>

There are also <a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:Tutorials" target="_blank">several other tutorials</a> and a <a href="<%= WontoMedia.help_url_prefix -%>WmHelp:GlossaryAtoO">glossary</a> of wontology terms.

  </p><p>

Please contact us on our
<a href="http://rubyforge.org/forum/?group_id=7903">forum</a> or
<a href="http://rubyforge.org/mail/?group_id=7903">email list</a>
with questions or comments.

  </p>
